"NOT FOUND"|"habent sanctum] the use of habeo with the passive participle denotes the abiding result of the action of the verb: ***they have (it) enacted***: contrast equitatum coegerat ***he had collected the cavalry *** with equitatum coactum habebat ***he had the cavalry collected***. This form is of course the origin of the modem French perfect; t.g.fai fait***habeo factum."

