"NOT FOUND"|"exaudiunt] * catch the sound of. exaudire is to catch a sound coming from any quarter. This is, I believe, a more correct explanation than that usually given, that the word means ***to hear clearly': cf. v. 30 et id clariore voce ut magna pars militum exaudiret where the meaning is ***that his words might reach them'. Cic. Acad. II. 20 quam multa quae nos fugiunt in cantu exaudiunt in eo genere exercitati***, ***catch***."

