"NOT FOUND"|"nunc quod...comparant-] on the reading of this passage see appendix. The general sense seems to be:******At the present day, since the uermans live the same hard life as they used to live, while the Gauls have been enervated by the luxury of the neighbouring provinces, they (the Gauls) have learnt by the experience of several battles to consider themselves no longer a match for the Germans***. Thus the protasis of the sentence ends at largitur, and the apodosis begins at paulalim."

