"NOT FOUND"|"palmae ratnique] Caesar evidently compares the palmated extremity of reindeers*** horns to the palm of the hand. Such a comparison would suggest itself to any one who had ever seen them. Nilsson, Skandi- navisk Fauna, Daggdjuren, p. 502, calls them ***flathandslika*, i.e. like the palm of the hand, so most other descriptive zoologists in terms almost similar. These ***palms*** end in finger-like prolongations, the rami of Caesar, and ***tines* (A. S. tan = twig) in the technical language of those who have to do with deer. Cf. Pliny XI. 37. 45 sparsit {natura cornua)"

